---
title: Picker Group
---

p.-text
  | Picker groups are used to wrap a series of pickers on a single line.

h3 Examples
h4 Base
p.-text To render a picker group, wrap a series of pickers in a div and apply the class <code>m-pickerGroup</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup
      each type in ['Radio1','Radio2','Radio3']
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id=`ia-${type}`)
        label(for=`ia-${type}`)
          = type
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup">
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio1">
      <label for="radio1">
        Radio1
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio2">
      <label for="radio2">
        Radio2
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio3">
      <label for="radio3">
        Radio3
      </label>
    </div>

